title: Beyond Provenance: Possible Afro Futures on the Blockchain
description: Two floors of self-identified Black Crypto Artists, each with easily accessible audio descriptions made by each artist about the themes and contexts of their works. The galleries are organized by the movements: AfroFuturism, Pop-Art, Abstraction, Fantasy and Self-Portriture. The exhibition was organized by One/Off including artists from 17 countries and is a not to be miss exhibition. The quality of both the work and curation is consistent throughout, making a statement about the future of online exhibition making.

title: THIRST ART
description: Les Houches, located 6 kilometres from Chamonix, is a ski resort with a domain which extends from an altitude of 950 metres up to 1900 metres. Long descents through tree-lined slopes are combined with impressive views of the Mont Blanc massif and the Chamonix valley. Les Houches is twinned with the Russian villages of Sochi and Krasnaya-Polyana and was chosen by the International Olympic Committee to assist in the organization of the 2014 Winter Olympic Games. Watch for more fun facts!

title: Frewuhn
channel: CAMHLAB: Contemporary Art Museum of Houston
description: Frewuhn’s Freedom Summer Mixtape Temple is an immersive digital gallery showcasing archival mixed media works created during the artist’s CAMHLAB (Contemporary Art Museum Houston) residency. This virtual space features in-depth artist interviews, panel discussions, recorded performances, and sound installations designed for viewers to experience inside the ONE / OFF Black Arts District on Cryptovoxels. Explore the Temple and meet with Frewuhn to ask questions about her work, process, and residency at CAMH. These panel discussions which can be watched through embedded Youtube's, pose the question, how do we define protest? And how can these definitions be reimagined for the future?  Follow CAMH’s Instagram (@camhouston) for more information about Frewuhn’s work with the future of protest and how to engage with this digital world.

title: Zach Murray
